i''\n|\n* Green Series\n|\nSeveral Specimens\n|\nA [[Coleoptera]]n of the family [[Carabidae]].\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==Vertebrata==\n=== Fishes ===\n====Actinopteri====\n{| class = \"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Genus\n! Species\n! Stratigraphic position\n! Material\n! Notes\n! Images\n|-\n|\n[[Saurorhynchus]]<ref>E. E. Maxwell and S. Stumpf. 2017. Revision of Saurorhynchus (Actinopterygii: Saurichthyidae) from the Early Jurassic of England and Germany. European Journal of Taxonomy 321:1-29</ref>\n|\n*''Saurorhynchus hauffi''\n|\n* Green Series\n|\nMultiple specimens.\n|\nThe youngest representative of the family [[Saurichthyidae]], known for its large jaws, similar to modern [[Belonidae]].\n|\n[[File:Saurorhynchus brevirostris.JPG|thumb|center|125px|''[[Saurorhynchus]]'']]\n|-\n|\n[[Grimmenichthys]]<ref name=\"Konwert\">Konwert, M., & H\u00f6rnig, M. (2018). Grimmenichthys ansorgei, gen. et sp. nov. (Teleostei, \u201cPholidophoriformes\u201d), and other \u201cpholidophoriform\u201d fishes from the early Toarcian of Grimmen (Mecklenburg-Western Pomerania, Germany). Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology, 38(3), e1451871. doi:10.1080/02724634.2018.1451871</ref>\n|\n*''Grimmenichthys ansorgei''\n*''Cf. Grimmenichthys ansorgei''\n|\n* Green Series\n|\nGG 439/1, articulated, but incompletely preserved specimen\n|\nA member of the [[Pholidophoriformes]].\n|\n|-\n|\n[[Pholidophoriformes]]<ref name=\"Konwert\" />\n|\n*''Pholidophoriformes indet.''  \n|\n* Green Series\n|\nGG 439/2\n|\nNon assigned to an especific genus\n|\n|-\n|\n[[Pholidophorus]]<ref name=\"Lehmann1\">Lehmann, U. (1971). Faziesanalyse der Ahrensburger Liasknollen auf Grund ihrer Wirbeltierreste. Mitteilungen aus dem Geologischen Institut der Technischen Universit\u00e4t Hannover, 10, 21-42.</ref>\n|\n*''Pholidophorus sp.''  \n|\n* Ahrensburg erratic assemblage<ref name=\"Lehmann1\" />\n|\nFragmentary remains\n|\nNon assigned to an especific species\n|\n[[File:Pholidophorus NT.jpg|thumb|center|125px|''[[Pholidophorus]]'']]\n|-