\"GlobalDataLab\">{{Cite web|url=https://hdi.globaldatalab.org/areadata/shdi/|title=Sub-national HDI - Area Database - Global Data Lab|website=hdi.globaldatalab.org|language=en|access-date=2018-09-13}}</ref><br/>{{color|#0c0|high}} \u00b7 [[List of regions of North Macedonia by Human Development Index|1st of 8]]\n| website                         = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} -->\n| footnotes                       = \n| coordinates                     = \n| area_urban_footnotes            = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_rural_footnotes            = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n| area_metro_footnotes            = <!-- <ref> </ref> -->\n}}\n\nThe '''Skopje Statistical Region''' ({{lang-mk|\u0421\u043a\u043e\u043f\u0441\u043a\u0438 \u0440\u0435\u0433\u0438\u043e\u043d}}, {{lang-sq|Rajoni i Shkupit}}) is one of eight [[Statistical regions of North Macedonia]]. Skopje, located in the north of the country, borders [[Kosovo]] to the north. Internally, it borders the [[Vardar Statistical Region|Vardar]], [[Polog Statistical Region|Polog]], [[Northeastern Statistical Region|Northeastern]], [[Eastern Statistical Region|Eastern]], and [[Southwestern Statistical Region|Southwestern]] statistical regions.\n\n==Municipalities==\n[[File:Map of the municipalities of Skopje Statistical Region en.svg|300px|right|thumb|The municipalities of the region]]\nThe region consists of the [[Skopje|City of Skopje]] and the following municipalities:\n*[[Ara\u010dinovo Municipality|Ara\u010dinovo]]\n*[[\u010cu\u010der-Sandevo Municipality|\u010cu\u010der-Sandevo]]\n*[[Ilinden Municipality|Ilinden]]\n*[[Petrovec Municipality|Petrovec]]\n*[[Sopi\u0161te Municipality|Sopi\u0161te]]\n*[[Studeni\u010dani Municipality|Studeni\u010dani]]\n*[[Zelenikovo Municipality|Zelenikovo]]\n\n==Demographics==\n[[File:Ethnic groups in Skopje Region of North Macedonia en.svg|thumb|right|300px|Map of the majority ethnic groups in the region]]\n\n===Population===\nThe current population of the Skopje Statistical Region is 578,144 citizens, according to the last population census in 2002, accounting for 28.6% of the total national population. The region is the largest by population in North Macedonia.\n\n===Ethnicities===\n{| border=1 cellpadding=4 cellspacing=0 class=\"toccolours\" style=\"align: left; margin: 0.5em 0 0 0; border-style: solid; border: 1px solid #7f7f7f; border-right-width: 2px; border-bottom-width: 2px; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- \n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" |\n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" align=\"center\" | <small>Number</small>\n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" align=\"center\" | <small>%</small> \n|- \n| style=\"background:#c1c1c1;\" | '''TOTAL'''\n| style=\"background:#c1c1c1;\" | '''578,144'''\n| style=\"background:#c1c1c1;\" | 100 \n|- \n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Macedonians (ethnic group)|Macedonians]]\n| 367,413\n| 63.6\n|- \n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Albanians]]\n| 133,893\n| 23.2\n|- \n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Romani people|Roma]]\n| 23,903\n| 4.1\n|-\n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Serbs]]\n| 18,051\n| 3.1\n|-\n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Turkish people|Turks]]\n| 12,123\n| 2.1\n|-\n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | [[Bosniaks]]\n| 10,880\n| 1.9\n|- \n| style=\"background:#F5F5DC;\" | others \n| 11,881\n| 2.1 \n|}\n\n<br/>\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Regions of Macedonia}}\n{{Skopje}}\n\n{{coord|42.0000|N|21.4333|E|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Statistical regions of North Macedonia]]\n[[Category:Geography of Skopje]]\n[[Category:Ara\u010dinovo Municipality]]\n[[Category:\u010cu\u010der-Sandevo Municipality]]\n[[Category:Ilinden Municipality]]\n[[Category:Petrovec Municipality]]\n[[Category:Sopi\u0161te Municipality]]\n[[Category:Studeni\u010dani Municipality]]\n[[Category:Zelenikovo Municipality]]\n", "text_old": "{{Refimprove|date=June 2019}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n<!-- See Template:Infobox settlement for additional fields and descriptions -->